Use bun instead of npm. `bun run dev` starts the developer server at the port specified in package.json.

This is a nuxt 3 project with autoimport; you don't need to explicitly import vue function or local components and composables.

Do not add any styles unless I explicitly ask for them. Minimal and essential layout is okay (e.g. flex/grid).

Do not use reactivity (ref/computed) unless it is necessary. Minimize the number of reactive state variables.

Avoid the usage of redundant guards. If a guard is applied downstream or upstream, don't apply it redundantly.

Do not add guards that simply skip over situations that could cause problems. Address the problem instead.
This goes especially for when I am asking you to fix a bug.

If assumptions are violated, throw an error. Do not provide fallbacks.

Write concise and succinct code. Implement the minimal version that satisfies my specification. Do NOT add additional features without approval. You can, however, suggest adding them in the chat.

Prefer functional style over imperative, e.g. maps over loops. The Remeda library is globally available as `R`.

Use VueUse composables whenever possible. These are documented below.


